# Regression: under JIT/OSR the emitted OP_LINE must stamp g_trace_current_line
# (the line prev_record_assign records into the history tape), mirroring the
# interpreter's CASE(LINE). A deep loop (past the 5000 OSR threshold) assigns x
# on a fixed line; `what is x at <line>` / `state_at` must return the LAST value
# written there, not the value frozen at the point the OSR thunk took over.
# Pre-fix the JIT skipped the stamp and these queries froze (e.g. 4999).
load_file of "lib/test.eigs"
x is 0
k is 0
loop while k < 20000:
    x is k
    k is k + 1
assert_eq of [what is x at 11, 19999, "JIT temporal: at-line correct under OSR"]
sa is state_at of 11
assert_eq of [sa["x"], 19999, "JIT temporal: state_at correct under OSR"]
test_summary of null
